      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AUTUMN WINTER (1) turned in a solid first-up effort at this track over 1625m and then was close up again last time at Hawkesbury over 1800m. He'd been off the scene for a long while and has more to give over the middle distance. The former Irish galloper is ready to win. RITA'S PEARL (6) followed a near miss this track/trip with a solid effort at Newcastle in strong. Peaks today and maps for a soft run. A live chance. PROCEAN (4) can show more for the Waller yard. Hasn't been having the best of luck, and it won't surprise to see him in the finish.  PHAROAH QUEEN (7) can improve second-up over more ground. SO PRECISE (8) may be the best of the remainder.",
